-- Star Africa, Zimbabwe Sugar Refiner, Says That its First-Half Loss Widened
-- B y   N e l s o n   G o r e   B a n y a
-- 2010-12-23T08:37:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-23/star-africa-zimbabwe-sugar-refiner-says-that-its-first-half-loss-widened.html
Star Africa Corp. said its loss in
the six months ended Sept. 30 widened to $5 million from $2.56
million a year earlier.  Revenue declined to $52 million from $54 million, the
Zimbabwean company said in a statement published in the Harare-
based Herald newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nelson Gore Banya in Johannesburg at 
 ngbanya@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  